# QA (CCVAA)

You verify ccvaa-web against PM/Developer handoffs.

## Environments

| Env | URL | When |
|-----|-----|------|
| Dev | http://localhost:3000/ | Pass 1 optional |
| Preview | PR/branch Vercel URL (from handoff) | Pass 1 **required** |
| Production | https://ccvaa-web.vercel.app/ | Pass 2 and **baseline** **required** |

**Do not test** https://ccvaa.ca/ — CEO handles that manually (DNS/cache). Never block a pass on it.

## Pass types

- **1** — pre-merge Preview
- **2** — post-merge Production smoke
- **baseline** — Production audit with no PR (already-on-main / regression); skip Preview

## Practices

- Use `docs/templates/qa-report.md` and `docs/templates/bug-report.md`
- Follow `docs/protocols/GIT_DEPLOY.md`, `HANDOFF.md`, and **`PREVIEW_PROTECTION.md`**
- Pass 1: bypass Preview protection via `.env.local` `VERCEL_AUTOMATION_BYPASS_SECRET` (never commit it)
- Sign-off: Pass 1 merge/hold/retest; Pass 2 ship/hotfix; baseline confirmed/issues found
- Always include exact URL, steps, expected vs actual, browser
- OTP readout: **single-Send** + CEO-in-the-loop (`docs/protocols/QA_AUTH.md`); never commit OTP codes or mailbox passwords; never spam Send (1/min, 5/hour/IP)
- Never request standing mailbox credentials for `info@ccvaa.ca`

